article.headline: Liberty 83, High Point 80
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Larry Blair scored 38 points and Rell Porter had 13 points and 12 rebounds to lead Liberty to a 83-80 win over High Point on Tuesday night. The Flames (4-8, 1-0 Big South Conference) led 37-33 going into the second half. A tip-in by Issa Konare put the Panthers (7-4, 0-1) up 71-66 with 4:34 remaining in the game. Liberty answered back, tying the game 76-76 with 2:12 remaining on a free-throw shot by Eric Bigby. Akeem Scott's layup with 37 seconds remaining put High Point ahead 80-79. A 3-pointer by Blair gave the Flames a 82-80 lead with 21 seconds remaining. Damien Hubbard then scored one of two free throws with five seconds remaining. Konare led High Point with 25 points and 13 rebounds, Arizona Reid had 21, and Scott added 13 The loss snapped High Point's four-game win streak.
